        <div type="recipe">
        <p> Blanch and beat a Pound of Almonds; put in just Rose-Water enough to keep them from Oiling; then take a Pound of fine Sugar, and boil it to a Candy; and when it is almost at a Candy Height, put in the Almonds; stir them over a cool Fire ’ till it is a very dry stiff Paste, and almost cold, and set it by ’ till it is quite cold; then beat it well in a Mortar, and put to it a Pound and a Half of fine sifted Sugar; rub it very well together, and make it up with a Spoonful of well-steep ’ d Gum-Dragon and Whites of Eggs, whip ’ d to a Froth; then squirt it, and bake it in a cool Oven; put into the Sweet-Almonds the Rind of a Lemmon grated, but none in the Bitter : If you don ’ t make the first Paste stiff, they will run about the Oven. Bake them on Papers and Tin-Plates. </p>
            </div>
